The paper deals with the application of deep neural networks to perform Bayesian reasoning on complex tasks. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and computational linguistics (cs.CL). However, since the paper focuses more on the application of deep learning to Bayesian reasoning, the sub-categories of machine learning and artificial intelligence are the most likely, followed by computer vision, neural and evolutionary computing, and computational linguistics.
